<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="523" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1047,1469]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1156,1181]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the three specimens mentioned above. 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[1121,1436,1156,1181]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[1369,1428,1156,1181]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
ressurected 
<taxonomicName box="[284,433,1193,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,433,1193,1216]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Myrmecopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including in it several species that were previously placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1135,1281,1191,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1281,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Pseudosphex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see notes on 
<taxonomicName box="[151,221,1228,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis box="[151,221,1228,1252]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[284,396,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deceptans">
<emphasis box="[284,396,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">deceptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, they did not treat 
<taxonomicName box="[760,934,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Abrochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spitzi">
<emphasis box="[760,934,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Abrochia spitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or its putative sister species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dukinfield-Jones, 1914" authorityName="Dukinfield-Jones" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nivaca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Pseudosphex nivaca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dukinfield-Jones" box="[242,513,1263,1288]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" refString="Dukinfield-Jones, E. (1914) New species of Lepidoptera-Heterocera from Brazil. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, no volume assigned, 1 - 12 + 1 pl." type="book chapter" year="1914">
Dukinfield-Jones, 
<number box="[453,513,1264,1288]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The two characters found by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[871,1193,1263,1288]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[1126,1185,1263,1288]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to be autapomorphic for 
<taxonomicName box="[194,343,1301,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[194,343,1301,1324]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Myrmecopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not occur in 
<taxonomicName box="[545,635,1301,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Abrochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spitzi">
<emphasis box="[545,635,1301,1324]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">P. spitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species may be closest to 
<taxonomicName authority="Draudt, 1915" authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1915" box="[1020,1323,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cercocladia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1157,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Cercocladia</emphasis>
Draudt, 
<number box="[1264,1323,1300,1325]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="1915.0">1915</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but until further studies are made, it should remain in 
<taxonomicName box="[652,798,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[652,798,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Pseudosphex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as incorrect as this placement may be.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1047,1469]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[199,536,1372,1397]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[469,528,1372,1397]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly mentioned 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1818" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1818" box="[817,1137,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,963,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Pseudosphex</emphasis>
Hübner, 
<number box="[1081,1137,1372,1396]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="1818.0">1818</number>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[151,286,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Chrysostola</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer, 
<number box="[500,559,1407,1432]" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" value="1855.0">1855</number>
, whereas the opposite is true, and for this reason this species is treated here under 
<taxonomicName box="[221,367,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[221,367,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="523">Pseudosphex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
